    {% if project_domain_name or project_domain_id }
    project_domain_name = {{ project_domain_name or project_domain_id }}
    ...

because you don't want to write these lines at all if there is nothing on the relation data. Does that make sense?

I'd almost be tempted to clean the logic here up a bit by removing the `if`s entirely and just do:

    project_domain_name = {{ manila_plugin.authentication_data.project_domain_name or manila_plugin.authentication_data.project_domain_id }}
    user_domain_name = {{ manila_plugin.authentication_data.user_domain_name or manila_plugin.authentication_data.user_domain_id }}

